flowRoot.flowPara: Here I've CLONED (i.e. ALT-D) each of the glyphs and placed them on top of each other here. Clone, vs duplicate, simply tells it to reuse the source paths, etc, not to create a copy. This is helpful because I can align them in relation to each other as they will be used on my card as well as I can edit the source glyph above and have the results show up everywhere it's used.
Here I've drawn the suit glyphs I'll use. I've given them id's ending in "Source" so I can easily find them in the XML editor. I've also moved them to the "AssetsLayer".
